==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cablelaid
<hw>Ca"ble*laid`</hw> <pr>(-l⟦amac⟧d`)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>Composed of three three-stranded ropes, or
hawsers, twisted together to form a cable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Twisted after the manner of a cable; <as>as, a
<ex>cable-laid</ex> gold chain</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Simmonds.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cablet</ent>⟦br⟧
